'''Chris Breikss''' is a Canadian businessman and university lecturer.<ref name=CB/><ref name=6S/><ref name=UBCBio/> An early adopter of [[internet marketing]] and [[search engine optimisation]], he leads [[Vancouver]]-based [[6S Marketing]].<ref name=CB/><ref name=6S/>

The paternal grandson of noted pre-[[World War II]] Latvian poet and patriot [[Leonids Breikss]],<ref name=CanLatOlym/> whilst attending [[Braemar Elementary School]] he appeared as an extra in an edition of ''[[MacGyver]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c2vNQP3wogw|title=''MacGyver''}}</ref> After graduating [[Carson Graham Secondary School]],<ref name=NVGOL>{{cite news|title=NV Grads zoom online|author=Michael Becker|publisher=North Shore News|date=9 November 1998}}</ref> Breikss then attended [[Capilano University]] on a Business Administration program, but left to train as an accountant.<ref name=CB/><ref name=VVNL/>

Having built his first website in 1994,<ref name=CB/> Breikss launched his first high traffic website of public note in 1998,<ref name=VVNL>{{cite news|title=Virtual Vancouver Night Life|author=Michael Becker|publisher=North Shore News|date=9 November 1998}}</ref> before joining Stratford Internet Technologies Inc.<ref name=NVGOL/> He then launched DiscoverVancouver.ca, and used it in 2000 to successfully lobby via a 25,000 signature petition the continuation of the annual [[Symphony of Fire]] fireworks event through commercial sponsorship, after [[Canadian federal government]] tobacco advertising restrictions had been implemented;<ref>{{cite news|title=Support Symphony of Fire on-line|author=Kevin Kinghorn|publisher=[[Vancouver Courier]]|date=1 March 2001}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Website sparks support for Symphony of Fire|publisher=The Province|date=19 February 2001}}</ref> the event is now sponsored by [[HSBC]]. In 2005, Breikss and his friend/business partner John Blown sold both DiscoverVancouver.ca and online reservations software company [[OnRes Systems]].<ref name=BiV40/>

Having launched 6S Marketing in 2000 in partnership with Blown,<ref name=BiV40>{{cite web|url=http://www.pdf.investintech.com/preview/8f20c1bc-641f-11e3-95e2-003048d80846/index.html|title=40 under 40: John Blown & Chris Breikss|publisher=Business in Vancouver|date=5 January 2009|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref> the company's team of 30 digital marketers are based in offices in Vancouver and [[Toronto]], with a company turnover of Can$10M.<ref name=CB>{{cite web|url=http://chrisbreikss.com/|title=Chris Breikss|publisher=ChrisBreikss.com|date=23 December 2013|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref><ref name=6S>{{cite web|url=http://www.6smarketing.com/agency/|title=About Us <U+2013> Chris Breikss|publisher=[[6S Marketing]]|date=23 December 2013|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref><ref name=BiV40/> As a result, Breikss has spoken at various [[Google|Google Engage]] events globally,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chrisbreikss.com/google-engage-conferencevancouver/|title=Chris Breikss|publisher=Google Engage Vancouver|year=2011|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://chrisbreikss.com/google-engage-for-agencies-london-2012/|title=Chris Breikss|publisher=Google Engage London|date=November 2012|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.6smarketing.com/blog/google-partners-program/|title=Google Partners Worldwide Launch <U+2013> Toronto|publisher=[[6S Marketing]]|date=May 2013|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref> and appeared as an expert commentator on internet issues in national media.<ref>{{cite news|title=Death of a Webmaster|author=Brigitte Petersen|publisher=Business in Vancouver|date=10 July 2000}}</ref><ref>{{cite |title=Canadian Facebook Privacy Issues|publisher=Global News|author=Sophie Lui|date=5 September 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pdf.investintech.com/preview/1b01d29e-6438-11e3-95e2-003048d80846/index.html|title=Foursquare hits Vancouver|publisher=[[CBC News|CBC]]|date=September 2009|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=2010 Stats Canada Internet Usage Survey|author=Elanie Yong|publisher=Global TV|date=11 May 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Travel Cookies|publisher=[[CBC News]]|date=25 June 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Protecting Your Privacy|author=Anu Dawit-Kanna|publisher=[[CBC News]]|date=20 October 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Facebook Goes Public|publisher=[[CTV News]]|date=18 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=This Year's Super Bowl Ads are Bigger and Badder Than Ever|author=[[Robin Gill]]|publisher=[[Global National]]|date=1 February 2013}}</ref> Between 2012 and 2014, Breikss taught mobile strategy and marketing as an external lecturer at the [[University of British Columbia]].<ref name=UBCBio>{{cite web|url=http://cstudies.ubc.ca/a/Instructor/Chris-Breikss/1038/|title=Chris Breikss|publisher=[[University of British Columbia]]|date=23 December 2013|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref> After the [[Canadian Government]] accepted 6S Marketing into its Technology Accelerator Program, the company opened new subsidiary Sheng Li Digital in [[New York city]] in May 2014, with Breikss relocating there to manage the operations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.biv.com/article/20140526/BIV0121/140529928/-1/BIV0100/vancouvers-6s-marketing-opens-new-york-office-to-target-affluent-chinese-customers|title=Vancouver's 6S Marketing opens New York office|author=Tyler Orton|publisher=[[Business in Vancouver]]|date=May 26, 2014|accessdate=May 28, 2014}}</ref>

During the [[2010 Winter Olympics]] held in Vancouver, Breikss office became the unofficial base for the [[Latvian Olympic Committee|Latvian Olympic team]].<ref name=CanLatOlym>{{cite web|url=http://www.canada.com/story_print.html?id=3d29d3f5-f050-4478-a319-8805e30f36f8&sponsor=|title=Tragic tale prompts Canadian to fly Latvian flag|publisher=[[Vancouver Sun]]/Canada.com|date=13 February 2010|accessdate=23 December 2010}}</ref> As both his parents have suffered from cancer, Breikss has raised over Can$100,000 in support of various cancer charities.<ref name=CB/>

